<P>
   HAIR-DRUGTEST (New Orleans) _ De La Salle High School, a
parochial school, is one of a handful of schools around the country
that tests for student drug use by taking hair samples. The testing
has been a big success at De La Salle, with parents almost
unanimously in favor of it. Now, two public school principals want
hair testing at their schools. The ACLU, among others, is opposed.
By Christopher S. Wren.
</P>
