   (ART ADV: Photos [NYT10,14) has been sent to NYT photo clients.)
</P>
<P>
   MICH-GUN-POLITICS (Escanaba, Mich.) _ The popularity of hunting
and the nearly universal ownership of guns in northern Michigan
pose a dilemma for Rep. Bart Stupak, the four-term Democrat who
represents this sprawling, wooded region. Stupak had been one of
about 30 Democrats who consistently crossed party lines to oppose
gun control -- at least, until this spring. Dismayed by the recent
school shootings in Littleton, Colo., and near Atlanta, Stupak has
publicly suggested that he would vote for legislation this month to
require child-proof safety locks on guns, mandate background checks
at certain gun shows and ban the import of high-capacity ammunition
clips. A look at the pressures on one congressman on the issue. By
Keith Bradsher.
</P>
