<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Book tells tinkerers how to upgrade PCs
 &HT;    By Charles Haddad
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ This book is for those of you who are both interested
and have the inclination to mess with the inside of your PC. Called
``Upgrading Your PC,'' it offers illustrated guides on how to do
all kinds of things. Among those things are adding a multimedia
card, modem or CD-ROM drive. You can also use this book to upgrade
your PC's microprocessor and add memory. Published by Jamsa Press,
the book retails for $26.95.
</P>
<P>
   You've heard of the Dow Jones industrial average and the S&AMP;P
500. Now there's Wired magazine's own stock index, a list of 40
so-called new-economy companies. In its June issue, Wired says its
stock market index is up 81 percent in the past 12 months. Its
index includes companies such as Yahoo!, America Online, Microsoft,
Sun Microsystems and Intel.
</P>
<P>
   On CD-ROM
</P>
<P>
   If you transfer a lot of files over the Internet, you might want
to look at a new product called CuteFTP. FTP, of course, refers to
the File Transfer Protocol software that enables you to do that.
What CuteFTP offers is a simple, Windows-like format in which to
use FTP to move files. CuteFTP uses drag-and-drop technology,
allows remote access and includes an HTML editor. The creators
claim the software excels at transferring large files between
corporate offices.
</P>
<P>
   MacSoft has bundled new 3-D versions of some of the more popular
arcade Mac computer games on one CD-ROM. Called ``America's
Greatest Arcade Hits,'' this CD includes ``Tetra-madness,'' ``Munch
Man,'' ``Alien Invaders'' and ``Qube Jumper.''
</P>
<P>
   Online
</P>
<P>
   Getting ready to plan a summer trip? You might start your
research on the Internet. Yahoo! Internet Life recently published a
list of what it considers the best travel sites, and topping that
list is a site called Biztravel.com. The magazine says the site has
the ``deepest profile,'' ``intelligently books trips'' and is the
best for frequent fliers. You'll find the site at
www.biztravel.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
