<TEXT>
<P>
   AUS-GREIG Jane Greig's column used for June 8
</P>
<P>
   By Jane Greig
</P>
<P>
   Cox News Service
</P>
<P>
   AUSTIN _ Q: The manager of my apartment complex told us to move
out. He says only two people are allowed in a one bedroom apartment
_ not three people. Our next-door neighbors are four children and
two parents _ six people living there.
</P>
<P>
   Where can I report this problem (the one bedroom apartment with
six people)? _ U.R.
</P>
<P>
   A: ``A minimum of 70 square feet in a sleeping room is needed
for two people; for each person added to that sleeping room you
need an additional 50 square feet,'' says chief housing inspector
James Doyle.
</P>
<P>
   To report suspected violations of these minimum square footage
requirements, contact the city's inspection services office at
499-2875.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I recently purchased some petunias and noticed when I arrived
home that they were called ``Laura Bush.'' Could they possibly be
named after the First Lady of Texas? _ Diane Williams
</P>
<P>
   A: No coincidence. The Laura Bush petunia is technically Petunia
x violacea ``Laura Bush.''
</P>
<P>
   This prolific bloomer tolerates heat well (no political pun
intended) and produces purple flowers. During testing, the
temporary name for this offspring of the V.I.P. Petunia (Violet in
Profusion) was Junior (no pun intended No. 2).
</P>
<P>
   Petunias do not like water on their flowers. After a Texas rain,
petunias close up and appear wilted for a few days.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I'm getting the runaround from the city as to whom to talk to
about installing a traffic light at a dangerous intersection _ FM
1325 and Century Park Boulevard. The city says it's the Texas
Department of Transportation's responsibility and, surprise
surprise, the TxDoT says it's the city's job. _ Michelle Wallace
</P>
<P>
   A: The Texas Department of Transportation. Put your request in
writing to have the location studied: TxDoT, Traffic Operations
Office, P.O. Drawer 15426, Austin 78761-5426. This office studies
traffic signal locations in 11 different counties, so it may be a
while before this intersection is examined.
</P>
<P>
   Contact Jane Greig, author of ``Thanks for Asking,'' at P.O. Box
670, Austin 78767; (512) 445-3697; e-mail jgreigstatesman.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By The AMERICAN-STATESMAN, AUSTIN, TX
</P>
<P>
   AP-NY-06-10-99 1711E
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
