 &HT;    Calling all parents
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Parents can check out our new Web site,
www.ajc.com/nfk, to find activities to use with the NFK page each
Monday. You'll find short lessons for every story. There also will
be a major project to further explore our story of the week. Plus,
we'll offer ideas to help kids learn about the rest of the paper.
New lesson plans are posted every Saturday. You can download a copy
or we can e-mail the lesson to you.
</P>
<P>
   Stack 'em up!
</P>
<P>
   How many cookies can you stack in 30 seconds without using glue?
You can find out in the 1999 Oreo cookie stacking contest, which
may come to a grocery store near you through Aug. 15. Check for
dates and locations online at www.oreo.com or call 1-800-665-9673.
If you stack the highest, you could win a $20,000 U.S. Savings
Bond, a year's supply of Oreos and a walk-on role on ``Honey, I
Shrunk the Kids: The Television Show.'' Last year's 7-and-under
winner stacked 26. The 8- to-12-year-old winner stacked 29.
</P>
