<HEADER>
A0850 &Cx1f; var-z
u i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ELECTION-MONITORS-REV     06-14 1284
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ELECTION-MONITORS-REVIEW-620&AMP;ADD-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NURTURING DEMOCRACY FROM THE GRASS ROOTS 
</HEADLINE>
  (The Week in Review) 
(NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For use by special arrangement
only. Asian and European points: Call Karl Horwitz in Paris for
details and prices, phone: 47 42 17 11; fax: 47-42-80-44). Latin
American points: Call Olivia Vasquez in Los Angeles, phone:
310-996-0075; fax: 310-996-0089). 
(lb) 
 By SETH MYDANS   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   JAKARTA, Indonesia _ When he was a much younger man, Jose
Concepcion once found himself holding up a bullet and peering at it
through his thick glasses. ``They are shooting at us,'' he said,
more incredulous than afraid. That was 13 years ago in the
