<HEADLINE>
WHAT'S IN STORE  
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;    (To purchase this special one-shot feature from W magazine _ the
rate is not prohibitive _ contact New York Times Syndicate Sales
Executive DEBRA WEYDERT at (732) 390-4480; fax, 732-390-4697.)
 &HT;    
 &HT;    ---------------------FREE ART!----------------------
 &HT;    ONE COLOR SLIDE is available ELECTRONICALLY by E-MAIL. Please
specify that you want the art when you order the article.
 &HT;    ----------------------------------------------------
 &HT;    
 By THE EDITORS OF W MAGAZINE 
 c.1999 Fairchild Publications  
<TEXT>
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &LR;  &QC;
<P>
   Below, top retailers cite the hottest beauty products on
counters near you _ and they named names. The consensus? Low-key
pretty is the favored beauty philosophy. And don't forget the color
pink and skin care that puts you at ease.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SAKS FIFTH AVENUE &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; Deborah Walters, vice president, divisional merchandise manager for
cosmetics and fragrance. &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; COLOR &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   We're very excited about Nars Face Glow shimmer. It makes you
look like you just came out of the sun. Also, the Guerlain
Terracotta Shiny Shine in bronze or gold imparts a healthy,
sun-kissed look. From Stila, Convertible Color tinted cream for
lips and cheeks, All Over Shimmer and Illuminating Powder
Foundation are wonderful. Trish McEvoy's Girly collection features
very natural pinks.
 &UR; SKIN &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   There's a lot of growth in the mask category, and they're
popular for a wide age group. We like Sisley Radiant Glow Express
Mask with Clays for cleansing and Express Flower Gel for hydrating,
toning and firming. We also see growth hormones as the next vitamin
C. One we especially like is Osmotics Kinetin, which is made with
plant growth hormones. We're having very good response to American
Vitamin Company, Philosophy, Christian Dior Vitalmine and Lancome
Hydra Zen. Interesting and new is Talika, an eyelash treatment
product with liposomes that claims to help grow lashes. There's
also Source Ocean nail and hand care and Danielle Netelle's
AntiDistress Lotion.
 &UR; FRAGRANCE &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Lolita Lempicka is unique and the packaging is whimsical and
really appealing. Perfumes Isabell is a huge business. We also like
Anna Sui, both in color and fragrance, and Angel Innocent.
 &UR; HAIR &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Hair care is a high-growth area. Especially great is the new
Frederic Fekkai Sun Protectant Spray with shea butter and items
from Phytologie and J.F. Lazartigue.
</P>
<P>
   -----
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NORDSTROM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; Dale Crichton, executive vice president of cosmetics. &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; COLOR &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   We're seeing a lot of sheer washes of color and a lot of pink. A
good example is Lancome's spring collection, Candide, which
includes trios of pastel eye shadows. We think the blue shade is
very easy to wear. Good lip glosses to try are Bobbi Brown Lip
Shine and Prescriptives Grace Lipgloss.
 &UR; SKIN &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   We're hearing a lot about treating dull, stressed skin.
Prescriptives Vibrant brightens tired skin and gives you a rested
and healthy glow, as does the Shiseido Bioperformance Clarifying
Essence. Lancome Hydra Zen corrects skin imbalances caused by
stress.
</P>
<P>
   -----
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BERGDORF GOODMAN &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; Vicki Haupt, senior vice president and general merchandise
manager. &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; COLOR &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The big trend is a blushed and dewy face with natural-toned
lips. Bronzers continue to be very important and our favorite
bronzers include Guerlain Terracotta and Bobbi Brown Bronze Sticks.
For a natural and fresh look, we like Chantecaille Real Skin cream
foundation. As for color, Paula Dorf lip glosses in soft pinks are
nice, as is Laura Mercier's new powder blush in Cedar Rose.
 &UR; SKIN &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Simple regimes are important for skin, with an emphasis on
products rich in nutrients. We like Estee Lauder Renutriv Intensive
Lift Body Creme, which is chock-full of goodies that firm and
moisturize the body. Others that we like, and that are exclusive to
Bergdorf Goodman, include Jo Malone Skincare and Leanne Hirsh
Skincare with marine extracts.
 &UR; FRAGRANCE &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Fragrances are becoming more full-bodied. Some that we like
include Geoffrey Beene, S.T. DuPont, Fable and Lucien LeLong, whose
flacon incorporates a working timepiece.
</P>
<P>
   -----
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NEIMAN MARCUS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; Leslie Faust, vice president, divisional merchandise manager of
cosmetics and fragrances. &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; COLOR &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   One of the strongest messages is the color pink, from pink
mascara to a pink face shimmer from Bobbi Brown that's exclusive to
Neiman Marcus. Versace has a new foundation that's beautiful. It
looks like a really expensive jar of cream. The Versace mascara is
also a really good product.
 &UR; SKIN &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   We're very excited about technology in skin care, especially
from Awake. People are also adding serums to their routines,
particularly from ReVive, La Prairie and Creme de la Mer. Also
important in skin care are Eve Lom Dynamite Lotion, Sisley's masks
and Lancome Oligo Minerale, exclusive to Neiman Marcus in the U.S.
 &UR; FRAGRANCE &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   We're really excited about Fresh, including its Index and Life
fragrances, and about Creed.
</P>
<P>
   -----
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HENRI BENDEL &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; Laura Saio, cosmetics and fragrance buyer. &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; COLOR &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Pink will carry us through the summer, as will shine around the
eyes and around the face. Our Trish McEvoy business continues to
grow, especially her beauty ``planners.'' Laura Mercier's Secret
Camouflage concealer is her best-selling product.
 &UR; SKIN &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   We're so excited about the Mario Badescu skin-care line. It has
minimal packaging and is really basic, but it works. It has an
incredible cult following in New York, and it's our No. 1 requested
skin-care line. Also exciting are Recipes for the Skin treatment
products and the Bliss Spa dine.
 &UR; BODY &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Bloom products from Natalie Bloom, a young Australian
entrepreneur, cover the entire gamut of color, from lip color to
crayons for cheeks. Also great are her travel items and
aromatherapy lip balms and massage oil.
 &UR; FRAGRANCE &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   L'Artisan Parfumeur continues to be our top-selling fragrance
line. The new Comptoir Sud Pacifique fragrance, Kumquat, is a juicy
fragrance that's wonderful for summer.
</P>
<P>
   -----
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FRED SEGAL &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; Robin Coe-Hutshing, owner/buyer of the Essentials Boutique in Santa
Monica. &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; COLOR &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Last season's berry thing is gone and the glitter thing is gone.
Instead, there's lots of shimmer, such as the Stila All Over
Shimmer. Nars Galaxy Girl lipstick and Stila Kitten eye shadow are
shot with gold and give a very warm look for summer. A line that I
know will do very well is T. LeClerc. It's very sophisticated and
the packaging is gorgeous. Body &AMP; Soul's lip glosses are amazing _
really shiny, but they don't move around _ and their loose powder
is really nice. Also exciting is the Anna Sui color collection and
Origins As Good As It Gets.
 &UR; SKIN &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Even with no new product introductions, Kiehl's never seems to
stop. We're doing incredibly well with the oxygen and sun
protection products from Peter Thomas Roth. Their daily moisturizer
with an SPF of 20 is nonirritating and wonderful. The whole
Philosophy line is doing great.
 &UR; FRAGRANCE &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Perfect Veil fragrance from Creative Sensualization smells
like clean, naked skin and has a really devoted following. &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; c.1999 Fairchild Publications &QL;
</P>
