   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIAN-AMRY (Washington) _ Experts on Russian politics say the
defiant occupation of Kosovo's main aiport by 200 Russian soldiers
isn't a Russian army mutiny but instead reflects an effort by
President Boris Yeltsin to allay anti-western nationalism gripping
his nation. By STEWART M. POWELL And ERIC ROSENBERG.
</P>
