   INHOFE-PORNO (Washington) _ Supporters of gay rights advocate
James Hormel are accusing Sen. James Inhofe, R-Okla., of hypocrisy
because several of the senator's staffers downloaded pornography
off the Internet onto the Senate computer system. Inhofe has
opposed Hormel's nomination to be U.S. ambassador to Luxemborg on
moral grounds. By JUDY HOLLAND.
</P>
