   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN _ Republican lawmakers' loathing of President
Clinton drives them to distraction. They agree on no principles or
policies. Their only common bond is their unconcealed distrust of a
president they have been unable to destroy. Their selfish reaction
to his success in Kosovo was shameful. Once again Clinton had
slipped through their fingers just as they were about to close
their hands around his throat. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
