<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-MAIN _ PRISTINA, Yugoslavia _ Day Three of the NATO
peacekeeping mission in Kosovo was again tense, as more than 1,200
U.S. Marines began moving into their sector and American diplomats
struggled to find a compromise with Russia over its role in the
peacekeeping operation. The NATO commander of the Kosovo
peacekeeping force downplayed the loss of the Pristina airport to
the
</P>
<P>
   Russians, saying its tactical significance was overplayed. With
Kosovar Albanian rebels quick to use the ongoing Serb pullout to
take control of as much as possible of the province, the ethnic
Albanians still there continued their coming out party. Developing.
(Kunstel/Holmes, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   w/KOSOVO-RENEWAL _ TUSUS, Yugoslavia _ In this isloated suburb
of troubled Prizren there are already signs of renewal, as members
of the rebel Kosovo Liberation Army are busy cleaning up and
preparing the more than 50 burned-out homes here for the eventual
return of ethnic Albanians who had abandoned them over the past
several months. And on a day when tensions between Serb and NATO
forces continued all over Kosovo province, there were signs here of
the situation being defused. DEVELOPING. (Kaplow, Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-RACAK _ RACAK, Yugoslavia _ The atrocities that took
place in this small village in southern Kosovo province in January
were among the first to arouse the anger of the world towards the
Serb-led Yugoslav forces ethnic cleansing campaign. We visit this
devastated village and talk to some of the survivors. DEVELOPING.
(Albright, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   FATHERHOOD _ WASHINGTON _ Former Joint Chiefs of Staff Chairman
Colin Powell addresses the National Fatherhood Initiative's summit.
(Hill, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ Microsoft calls its first defense
witness in the rebuttal phase of the federal antitrust trial _ an
America Online executive who testified for the government in the
trial's first phase and who now will appear as a hostile witness.
(Glass, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-NH _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush campaigns in New Hampshire.
(Greenberger, Austin American-Statesman). 20-25.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: ETA 8 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   GORE _ NEW ORLEANS _ Vice President Al Gore addresses the U.S.
Conference of Mayors. (Konigsmark, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BAPTIST-CONVENTION _ The Southern Baptist convention starts
today and for the first time ever Austinites will be able to view
the action live over the internet. This year's convention has a
uniquely Austin flavor with Ralph Smith delivering the coveted
convention sermon and Joe Carroll, a minister at Hydle Park, in
charge of the music. Hyde Park pastor Kie Bowman spoke Sunday night
at the pastor's conference. (Perkes, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   WOODPECKER _ PINEHURST, N.C. _ During the U.S. Open, to be
played at the legendary Pinehurst No. 2 golf course, federal
wildlife officials will tout the success of a four-year-old program
to protect the habitat of the endangered red-cockaded woodpecker.
The ``Safe Harbor'' program, which began at Pinehurst No. 2, has
since been adopted by 24 more landowners in the North Carolina
Sandhills _ including nine golf courses _ and is being rolled out
as a national model. (Burritt, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
