   BAPTIST-VEGETARIANS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Southern Baptists have targeted other groups for
conversion in the past. Now, the tables are turned. This week, when
thousands of Baptists arrive in Atlanta for their national
convention, they will be greeted by a 60-foot by 20-foot billboard
declaring, ``Jesus Was a Vegetarian.'' ``We are taking our message
to Baptists that killing and eating animals is inherently
un-Christian,'' said Bruce G. Friedrich, a spokesman for People for
the Ethical Treatment of Animals. ``Jesus was the Prince of Peace,
not a butcher.'' By JIM JONES. Story has moved in ``a'' general
news category. &QL; 
