<P>
   HOCKEY-NEOPHYTES &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Hockey mania has struck deep and hard in North Texas.
There's the neighbor who doesn't know icing from high-sticking but
who, nevertheless, flies a Stars flag. The friends who are suddenly
hunkering down for hours in front of their TVs or who dicker with
scalpers for expensive seats. It's easy to explain, says historian
Jerry Rodnitzky. ``You want to identify with a winner.'' By BARRY
SHLACHTER. Story has moved in ``a'' general news category and ``s''
sports category. &QL; 
