</P>
<P>
   BUSH-DYNASTY &QL;
</P>
<P>
   KENNEBUNKPORT, Maine _ They have the same name, the same facial
expressions, the same family background. Now the son is seeking to
share a place in history with his father. Nearly 175 years after
John Quincy Adams followed his father into the White House, Texas
Gov. George W. Bush wants to do the same for his family. But don't
use the term ``dynasty'' around his dad. ``We never felt entitled
to something,'' former President Bush says. By RON HUTCHESON. Story
has moved in ``p'' politics category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   F I N A N C I A L &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
.MDBU/.MDNM/ SIX FLAGS-ADS &QL;
</P>
<P>
