<P>
   COKE-BELGIUM _ ATLANTA _ The Belgian government Monday banned
the sale of all beverages of the Coca-Cola Co. following more
reported cases of poisoning across the country. Health Minister Luc
Vandenbossche urged Belgians not to drink Coca-Cola and such
Coca-Cola brands as Fanta, Sprite, Aquarius and Bonaqua. On Monday,
40 students were hospitalized with symptoms of poisoning in
Lochristi in west Belgium. Last week, 31 school children became
nauseous in the town of Bornem after drinking Coca Cola and were
taken to hospital. (Unger, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ Microsoft calls its first defense
witness in the rebuttal phase of the federal antitrust trial _ an
America Online executive who testified for the government in the
trial's first phase and who now will appear as a hostile witness.
(Glass, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
