<P>
   &UR; SETTLEMENT IN THE BALKANS &LR;   &UR; (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   YUGO-GRAVES (Kacanik, Yugoslavia) _ As American soldiers stand
guard over what NATO officials say may be a mass grave of civilians
killed by Serb forces, returning refugees tell a chilling story of
how men, women and children were massacred more than two months
ago. By Kevin Cullen. 1400 words.
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA (Sarajevo, Bosnia-Herzegovina) _ Russian commanders
tell Western peacekeepers they will resupply their troops at the
Pristina Airport with a convoy from Bosnia. But they return to
their basecamp when orders to proceed to Kosovo fail to arrive.
Wrapup. By Charles A. Radin. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   YUGO-KLA (Prizren, Kosovo) _ Kosovo Liberation Army takes
control of two major neighborhoods, setting up a potential
political conflict with international peacekeeping troops and a
possible military clash with yet-to-depart Serb militia. By Susan
Milligan. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-BUSH (New Castle, N.H.) _ George W. Bush says he would
not require Supreme Court nominees to pass an anti-abortion
``litmus test,'' pledges to uphold the dignity of the presidency.
By Jill Zuckman and Michael Kranish. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-COURT-EXIT (Boston) _ State high court says police do not
automatically have the right to order the driver or passengers out
of a vehicle during a traffic stop. The 5-2 ruling ignores two US
Supreme Court rulings that took the opposite tack. By John
Ellement. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   EPA-POLLUTE (Undated) _ EPA says it will grant petitions from
four states that would require reductions of 717,000 tons of
smog-causing chemicals in 12 states. By Scott Allen. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   LEWIS-TRIAL (Boston) _ Former long-time Celtics season ticket
holder says he saw Reggie Lewis sniffing ``a shiny white powdered
substance'' in a public restroom at a pizza parlor in 1992. By
Sasha Pfeiffer. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   COMPUTERS-WORM (Undated) _ Computer support lines are
overwhelmed after new outbreaks of a virus that spreads not only by
e-mail, but through shared files on a network. By Hiawatha Bray.
500 words.
</P>
