<SLUG> BC-NYTIMES-COLUMNIST-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TIMES NAMES A COLUMNIST 
</HEADLINE>
  (also moved in `k' news file) 
(pr) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Gail Collins, an editorial writer for The New York
Times, has been appointed an Op-Ed Page columnist for the duration
of the 2000 political campaign.
</P>
<P>
   The announcement was made Monday by Arthur Sulzberger Jr., the
paper's publisher, and Howell Raines, the editorial page editor.
They said the assignment would draw on Ms. Collins' experience with
the political scene, both locally and nationally. Her column will
appear twice a week, and she will return to editorial writing after
the campaign.
</P>
<P>
   Before joining the editorial board in 1995, Ms. Collins, 53, was
a columnist at The Daily News from 1985 to 1991 and at New York
Newsday, from 1991 to 1995. She also worked as a financial
journalist for United Press International in New York from 1982 to
