<P>
   BC-INTELLIGENCE-REPORT-NYT (moved on Saturday, June 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday, June 12,
about possible hidden stocks of the smallpox virus misstated the
party affiliation of Senator John Glenn of Ohio, who headed a
committee that made public a Russian report on the virus. He is a
Democrat.
</P>
<P>
   BC-BANK-AMERICA-SHARE-NYT (moved on Friday, June 11)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, June 11,
about concerns over consumers' financial privacy referred
incompletely to the involvement of Memberworks, a telemarketing
firm based in Stamford, Conn., in a suit filed against U.S. Bancorp
by the Minnesota Attorney General's office. Although the suit
contends that the bank illegally sold credit histories and other
information to Memberworks, the firm is not a defendant in the
case.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MEDIA-TALK-NYT (moved on Sunday, June 13)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, June 13,
about the bidding for ``Aging With Grace,'' a book about nuns from
the order of the School Sisters of Notre Dame, misspelled the
surname of two elderly women to whose memoir it was compared. They
were the Delany sisters, not Delaney.
</P>
