r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBO-ARENA-LADN     06-14 0368
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBO-ARENA-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IS L.A. READY FOR THE ARENA `AVENGERS`?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Los Angeles' newest sports franchise got a name
and a face put to it Monday, and the mayor's designee to the
ceremony had but one wish. ``I don't know what the name is,'' said
senior adviser Steve Soboroff, ``but as long as it's not the
`Raiders,' I don't care.''
</P>
<P>
   While the Coliseum awaits a new, NFL-sanctioned tenant, the only
football team certain to call the city home is the Avengers of the
Arena Football League.
</P>
<P>
   Owner Casey Wasserman, granted the indoor league's 17th
franchise last fall, unveiled the Avengers name and logo _ a
futuristic-looking, helmeted warrior in blue, gold and red _ Monday
morning outside Staples Center.
</P>
<P>
   The Avengers, co-tenants with the Lakers, Clippers and Kings,
will begin play at Staples next April.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wanted a name that would ... capture the spirit and
imagination of Los Angeles,'' said the 24-year-old Wasserman. The
team name, he said, is ``an embodiment of ideals _ power,
excitement, unpredictability.''
</P>
<P>
   Wasserman, his advisers and marketing consultants considered
several names, and in the end, chose Avengers over Knights.
</P>
<P>
   All the team needs now is a coach and 20 players. Wasserman
hopes to hire a coach-general manager by the end of August, and
he'll be allowed to sign free agents after the ArenaBowl on Aug.
22. The roster will be filled out via an expansion draft in
November.
</P>
<P>
   Wasserman said he'll try to find a coach with NFL experience,
``maybe a name,'' but possibly a fresh face to go with the newborn
franchise.
</P>
<P>
   This will be L.A.'s second entrant in the Arena league. The
Cobras played one season at the Sports Arena in 1988, when the
fledging league was still struggling for an identity. Wasserman
expects better results and ambitiously envisions a sellout crowd of
18,500 at Staples for the Avengers' debut.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think I would have bought the team if I didn't think
that was achievabe,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Tickets are on sale by phone at 877-4-Avengers, and more
information is available online, at www.LAavengers.com.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-14-99 2311EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
